Data source: Deloitte
AI in IT & cybersecurity
The most popular use cases of AI in the development workflow include writing code (reported by
82% of developers surveyed), searching for answers (67.5%), and debugging (56.7%).
Statista
The most popular use cases of AI in cybersecurity are anomaly detection (cited by 56.9% of professionals
surveyed), malware detection (50.5%), and automated incident response (48.9%).
Statista
The cybersecurity areas where defensive AI is expected to impact the most include detecting new or unknown threats (according to 56.9 of professionals surveyed), detecting threats as a whole (55.3%), and
autonomously responding to threats (43%).
